President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Florida due to the impact of Hurricane Matthew. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work and hazard mitigation measures. Terry L. Quarles has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations. Damage surveys are still ongoing, and more counties and forms of assistance may be designated in the future. For further information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.